CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 14, 1962, pg. 9 reads: "More Out-Of-Towners - The Squaws' affair also drew this group of out-of-towners. Left to right, seated: Mrs. Earl Dunnings and Mrs. Walter Wheaton of Roanoke, Va., and Mrs. Floyd Keene of Washington, D.C.  Standing: Mr. and Mrs. Daniel T. Levert, Cleveland, Ohio; Earl Dunnings, Roanoke, Va.; Dr. and Mrs. Henry C. Edwards,  Washington, D.C.; Mrs. Pat Machen, Los Angeles, Calif.; Mr. and Mrs. Lawrence Washington, Cleveland, Ohio; Mrs. Robert Batch, Elizabeth, Pa., and Walter Wheaton, Roanoke, Va. - Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated, from left: Mrs. Earl Dunnings, Mrs. Walter Wheaton, and Mrs. Floyd Keene; standing, from left: Mr. and Mrs. Daniel T. Levert, Earl Dunnings, Dr. and Mrs. Henry C. Edwards, Pat Machen, Mr. and Mrs. Lawrence Washington, Mrs. Robert Batch, and Walter Wheaton, posed in Hilton Hotel for Squaw Club's "Cotton Extravaganza"
